s five disciplines: music, architecture, literature, painting, and sculpture.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly 40 years\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1246}, {\"ngram\": \"art competitions\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic program\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"five disciplines\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"architecture\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"literature\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"painting\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"sculpture\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually these Olympic competitions were discontinued in 1954 due to concerns about amateurism versus professionalism, but not before Olympic gold medals were awarded to nearly 50 participants.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these Olympic competitions\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1481}, {\"ngram\": \"amateurism\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"professionalism\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold medals\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 50 participants\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1924 Games were considered the apex of the Olympics' art era with almost 200 participants over all disciplines.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 1924 Games\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1613}, {\"ngram\": \"the apex\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' art era\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"almost 200 participants\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"all disciplines\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During these Games, Hungarian Alfred Hajos earned a silver in the architecture event, adding to his two swimming golds from the 1896 Games and becoming one of only two participants to ever win an Olympic medal in athletics and art.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9996180722643135, \"rank\": 0.0003801056162015269, \"text\": \"Hungarian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"the architecture event\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"his two swimming golds\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1896 Games\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1853}, {\"ngram\": \"only two participants\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1895}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Art wasn't without its controversies.\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Art\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1951}, {\"ngram\": \"its controversies\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 1984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1924 there were no medals awarded in the music competition-judges decided that none of the musical compositions was worthy of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no medals\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"the music competition-judges\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"the musical compositions\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Judges in architecture also did not award a gold medal that year.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Judges\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"architecture\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A short-lived Olympic competition within gymnastics, rope climbing only made it into four Olympics (in 1896, 1904, 1924, and 1932) before getting cut down after the 1932 Games.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A short-lived Olympic competition\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2229}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"rope climbing\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2262}, {\"ngram\": \"four Olympics\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1932 Games\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition format was simple: the athlete to climb to the top in the quickest time won.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2465, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The competition format\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2395}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2439}, {\"ngram\": \"the quickest time\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climbers could only scale the smooth, unknotted rope with their hands (no feet allowed), covering 25 feet (the 1896 Games required 41 feet of climbing and only two athletes reached the top).\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Climbers\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2474}, {\"ngram\": \"the smooth, unknotted rope\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"their hands\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2535}, {\"ngram\": \"no feet\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"25 feet\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1896 Games\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2587}, {\"ngram\": \"41 feet\", \"from\": 259